<TITLE> PM warns against river flow disruption </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 27 (bdnews24.com)  Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has warned of tough actions against those who disrupt the natural flow of rivers, quarry sands and cut off hills illegally. "Stern and prompt actions will be taken against those responsible for any disruption of rivers' natural flow. Land and water resources ministries are working on that," she told parliament on Wednesday during a question-answer session. The prime minister said the government is working to formulate a policy to check illegal sand quarrying. She answered three written queries out of five and few supplementary questions, as the session resumed at 3:10 pm with speaker Abdul Hamid in the chair. Hasina referred to an incident of putting barrier in river only for fishing and said: "We'll take stern actions against such acts We've to keep the navigability of the rivers" Mentioning that the government has taken various measures to face climate change and global warming, she said a fund of 100 million dollars has been received to that end. She said the government has formed a board for development of country's hoars. To a question by chief whip Abdus Shaheed, the prime minister said a plan has been taken to excavate rivers. "Dikes will be developed on both the banks of the rivers and trees planted." Answering a supplementary question by Meher Afroz Chumki, she said three ministries are working to formulate a policy, which would determine the quantum of sand to be quarried. Citing the deplorable conditions of the rivers Buriganga, Turag, Balu and Shitalakkhya, she said works on going on to remove waste from their beds. The prime minister said industrial waste would not be allowed to be disposed off in river
